2.00	John_Clifford_(choreographer)	John Clifford (choreographer)	John Clifford, is best known as the creator of “Casablanca, The Dance,” produced by Warner Bros. Theatre Ventures, Inc. and his Los Angeles Dance Theater, and founder / artistic director of the original Los Angeles Ballet (1974–1985), and the chamber sized touring ensemble, Ballet of Los Angeles (1988–1991). Before that time, however, Clifford was a world-renowned principal dancer and choreographer with George Balanchine’s New York City Ballet, (1966–1974) and guest artist from 1974–1981, and was widely considered to be Balanchine’s protégé (Saturday Review).	
